<activity><title>Evaluating and Solving</title>
<introduction><p>Use the graph of <m>y=2x-6</m> to complete the tasks.</p>
    <image source="act-1-2-1.png" width="40%"></image></introduction>
    <task><p>Evaluate <m>y=2x-6</m> when <m>x=-1</m>.</p>
        <p> <m>\blert{\text{Circle the point on the graph with} ~x=-1.}</m></p>
        <p> <m>\blert{\text{What is its}~y\text{-coordinate?}}</m></p></task>
    <task><p>Solve <m>y=2x-6</m> when <m>y=4</m>.</p>
        <p><m>\blert{\text{Circle the point on the graph with} ~y=4}</m>.</p>
        <p><m>\blert{\text{What is its} ~x\text{-coordinate?}}</m></p></task>     
    <task><p>Find the answers to parts (a) and (b) algebraically, and compare with the answers you obtained from the graph.</p></task>
</activity>

